HEADWORD: Protagonist
<hw>Pro*tag"o*nist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>prwtagonisth`s</grk>; <grk>prw^tos</grk> first +
<grk>'agonisth`s</grk> an actor, combatant, fr. <grk>'agw`n</grk> a
contest.]</ety> <def>One who takes the leading part in a drama; hence,
one who takes lead in some great scene, enterprise, conflict, or the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shakespeare, the <qex>protagonist</qex> on the great of modern
poetry.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

